{"title":"What should I ask Musa al-Gharbi?","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/903530006/0/marginalrevolution~What-should-I-ask-Musa-alGharbi.html","date":1724695863000,"content":"<p>Yes, I will be doing a Conversation with him.</p>\r\n<blockquote><p>Musa al-Gharbi is a sociologist and assistant professor in the School of Communication and Journalism at Stony Brook University. He is a columnist for The Guardian and his writing has also appeared in the New York Times, the Washington Post, and The Atlantic, among other publications.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>I am a big fan of his forthcoming book <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Have-Never-Been-Woke-Contradictions/dp/0691232601/ref=sr_1_1?crid=1R8EOHK0GBNPD&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.I7mMyO1Mp4_M3bRYyX-X-Q.FEDbDAVLk_CbgYsusPeQ_85q4L4Vmhto3BCSxBLhgYY&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=musa+al-gharbi+we+have+never+been+woke&amp;qid=1724681568&amp;sprefix=musa+al%2Caps%2C71&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">We Have Never Been Woke</a>, which I have blurbed.  Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://musaalgharbi.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Musa’s home page</a>, do read <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://musaalgharbi.com/musa-al-gharbi/biography/\" target=\"_blank\">his bio</a>.  Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://x.com/Musa_alGharbi?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor\" target=\"_blank\">Musa on Twitter</a>.</p>\r\n<p>So what should I ask?</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/08/what-should-i-ask-musa-al-gharbi.html\">What should I ask Musa al-Gharbi?</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"htt